title: 15th Annual Critical Diversity Studies Forum
description: Register NowWe are excited to share this year’s 15th Annual Critical Diversity Studies Forum on Thursday, October 2nd, 2:40p- 4:25p in McLaren. This theme in our celebratory year is "We Keep Us Safe.""We Keep Us Safe" is a call to action from community organizers, disability justice practitioners, abolitionists, queer, immigrant, and BIPOC communities who have demonstrated that we all deserve more safety and justice than our current systems provide.  In our increasingly uncertain and volatile times, we invite all of us to create true safety by nurturing relationships of collective care, mutual aid, and solidarity while refusing binaries of “us vs. them.”  “We Keep Us Safe" is an invitation to radically envision collective safety: as a shared responsibility to love and protect each other, especially those most impacted by injustice.This year’s Forum will feature Yosimar Reyes (writer, poet, performer and Santa Clara Poet Laureate), Terisa Siagatonu (award-winning poet, teaching artist, mental health educator, and community leader), and Zachary Norris (former executive director of the Ella Baker Center for Human Rights, author, organizer, and advocate).

title: ¡Sí Podemos!: Latiné Theology’s Resilience and Boldness
description: Cecilia González-Andrieu, president of the Academy of Catholic Hispanic Theologians of the United States and professor of theology at Loyola Marymount University, explores the relevance of Christian faith in a time of chaos and repression. For decades — and from the margins — Latiné theologians have accompanied and lifted up the community’s struggle for survival and dignity, developing insights born of endurance and rooted in lived experience. Today, these ways of seeing and acting hold lessons our whole society can no longer ignore and urgently needs.Co-sponsored by University Ministry, the Department of Theology and Religious Studies, and Casa Madríz Living Learning Community.Register Here »This event is open to all USF community members.

title: Navigating College Together: Supporting Your Student’s Journey
description: We’re excited to launch Navigating College Together: Supporting Your Student’s Journey, a workshop series created for USF parents and family members. Each session will offer practical tools, helpful insights, and campus resources to guide you in supporting your student’s success at USF. Sessions will be held virtually on Wednesdays at 5:30 PM.Zoom Meeting Link: https://usfca.zoom.us/j/84507763283Check out the schedule below - we look forward to the many conversations!Workshop #1:  Wednesday, September 24Workshop Title: When Homesickness Hits: What Families Need to KnowWorkshop Description: Starting college is a big step not only for students, but for families too. This interactive session will share practical tools and insights to help you support your student, while also giving you space to reflect on your own experience during this transition.Workshop #2:  Wednesday, October 1Workshop Title: Off-Campus Housing InformationalWorkshop Description: Please join us for an Off-Campus Housing 101 Workshop. We will talk about rent prices, neighborhoods, navigating the housing search process, booking individual appointments for support, and answer some of your questions.Workshop #3:  Wednesday, October 8Workshop Title: From Curriculum to Career: Why Internships and LinkedIn are the Keys to Your Student’s SuccessWorkshop Description:  Alex Hochman, the Senior Director of Career Services, will discuss why internships are critical for a student's long-term career success and show how USF students have access to thousands of unique internship postings. Also, prepare to be dazzled by LinkedIn strategies to find and utilize alumni mentors and employment opportunities.Workshop #4:  Wednesday, October 15Workshop Title: One Must Travel to Learn: Studying Abroad at USFWorkshop Description: Learn about international opportunities available to students for a semester, an academic year, or additional short-term options. The presentation will cover the application process, eligibility, costs, and programs available through USF. The second half of the workshop will feature study abroad returnees to share their experiences from abroad and answer any questions.Workshop #5: Wednesday, October 22Workshop Title: Anxiety Management -- Yours and TheirsWorkshop Description: In this session hosted by Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS), we will differentiate between stress, anxiety, and panic for you and your student. We will provide resources and practical exercises to combat everyday anxieties.Workshop #6: Wednesday, October 29Workshop Title: Jumpstart Your Wellness: A Family Guide to Student Health at USFWorkshop Description: Learn how Health Promotion Services (HPS) supports the well-being of the USF student body through a comprehensive range of programs and services. Dedicated to fostering a safe, healthy, and vibrant campus community, HPS empowers students to thrive personally and academically.

title: Mass of the Holy Spirit
description: The Mass of the Holy Spirit is a Jesuit tradition dating back to 1548. Celebrated yearly at Jesuit educational institutions worldwide, this tradition marks the beginning of the new academic year.This year, at USF, it will also celebrate the inauguration of President Salvador D. Aceves ’83, EdD ’95. It is an opportunity for our community to come together to pray for the guidance and wisdom of the Holy Spirit.The Mass will include prayers and blessings for President Aceves as he begins his leadership, asking for strength, clarity, and compassion in service to the university and its mission. All faiths and beliefs are welcome to celebrate this ancient Jesuit Catholic tradition — no registration required.This event is part of CelebrateUSF. Learn more about other events being hosted that weekend.This event is open to all USF community members.

title: Community Welcome BBQ
description: Following the Mass of the Holy Spirit, all are invited to continue the celebration at a community barbecue on Welch Field. title: Silk Speaker Series: Nicole Kidman
description: Register Now »The Silk Speaker Series Presents Nicole Kidman.Internationally recognized, award-winning actress and producer, Nicole Kidman joins us on Saturday, October 18 during the CelebrateUSF weekend for an evening conversation.   Thought leaders, elite athletes, diplomats, inventors, and more have come to the Silk Speaker Series at USF, but this time, Nicole Kidman makes her debut.From her iconic roles in Moulin Rouge!, The Hours, Big Little Lies, and more recently Nine Perfect Strangers and BabyGirl, to her work as a global advocate for women’s rights and mental health, Nicole Kidman brings a powerful voice and perspective to the Hilltop.This is your chance to hear her speak candidly about her career, creativity, activism, and the stories that have shaped her life—both on and off the screen.Seats are limited. Secure your seat and RSVP today.This event is part of CelebrateUSF. Learn more about other events being hosted that weekend.The Silk Speaker Series at the University of San Francisco invites thought leaders in business, culture, and global affairs to share their wisdom and ideas with students, alumni, faculty, and friends of the university. Learn more »

title: Relationship Violence Awareness Month Resource Tabling Fair
description: October is Relationship Violence Awareness Month, and here at USF, we want to share information about how to support survivors in our community and the resources available for students, faculty, and staff. We have invited local Bay Area organizations, including CUAV, Black Women Revolt, La Casa De Las Madres, and One Love, and we plan to provide activities and resources that students can access. Additionally, it helps bring awareness to what healthy and unhealthy relationships look like and how to support a friend who might be experiencing partner violence.

title: Clip, Cut, Connect for BIPOC Mental Wellness Program
description: Take time for the Clip, Cut, Connect for BIPOC Mental Wellness event. Students can enjoy free haircuts and connect in a welcoming space.Professional barbers and stylists from ClipDart are thrilled to be back on campus, offering more than just haircuts, but a chance for you to unwind, share out, and build community.   Whether you're getting a cut or simply stopping by, take this time to relax, engage, and prioritize your well-being.You can reserve your spot in advance or drop by on the day of to check availability. Save Your Spot »For the best results, arrive with clean, product-free hair.Sponsored by Health Promotion Services. With support from the Cultural Centers and BASE. This event is open to all USF community members.

title: USF's Day of the Dons
description: MAKE A DON'S DAY. MAKE A DON'S LIFE.Day of the Dons is here, USF's biggest fundraising campaign of the year! Ride the wave with us today as we celebrate the power and generosity of our community coming together to support causes that you care about! From fostering inclusivity to supporting climate initiatives, you have the opportunity to support causes that you hold close to your heart, and inspire USF students to take action on addressing these important issues of our generation. No matter what the amount, every gift counts on the Day of the Dons.Thank you for your support. You are making a lifelong impact!See more:https://www.usfca.edu/giving/day-of-the-dons

title: Day of the Dons Celebration
description: Join the USF community in coming together on Day of the Dons — our special day to experience the transformative power of giving.

title: 7th Annual Women of Color Leadership Conference
description: The Cultural Centers and the Office of Antiracism, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (ADEI) are excited to present the sixth annual University of San Francisco Women of Color Leadership Conference. Our conference is FREE and open to the public, featuring women of color affiliated with the University of San Francisco who facilitate various sessions centered in women of color leadership, empowerment, freedom dreaming, and liberation.

title: USF Market Day
description: Fresh food and produce, farmer's market style!Shop FREE produce from Star Route Farms while sampling local products and enjoying music from a live KUSF DJ! You can also learn more about USF's Food Pantry, ASUSF Senate, Office of Sustainability, Bon Appetit programs, and Student Leadership and Engagement (SLE).

title: USF Earth Day Celebration
description: Join the fun as more than four dozen campus and local organizations showcase their mission, foster connections within the community, and provide educational resources to the USF community. There will also be food, activities, live music, and adorable goats for everyone to enjoy.
